  <abstract>The Honorable Discharge Certificate for Spencer S. Ferguson includes a physical description and was signed by Capt. Jos. B. Gibson, Camp Jackson, S.C. This discharge was issued for the expiration of his term of service. Ferguson was born at Little Lot, Tenn. in Hickman County and was a farmer when he enlisted at age 24. He served in the Ordnance Battalion from April 27, 1918 to Feb. 8, 1919" "Service honest and faithful." Vaccinations are listed.</abstract>
